SubString.CExoString: Your message is inscribed on this paper. You may post it on any bulletin board.
This door is sturdy and almost impossible to picklock or climb over. Maybe some specific halfling female carrying bastard sword and katana could make it.
A portal glows softly before you. You wonder where it leads.
A portal glows softly before you. You wonder where it leads.
A bulletin board to read and post messages. A scribe is needed to write a message.
A bulletin board to read and post messages. A scribe is needed to write a message.
A holy symbol, it may also be used to attack, but very poorly.
Provides a temporary +5 bonus to Open Locks and +10 bonus to Search, Disable Trap, Move Silently, Pick Pockets, Set Trap, and Hide
Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Faerun.
This is an oil flask. You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
The kit is full of herbs, salves, bandages, and other useful material. It may be used to stop bleeding, cure poison or disease, and increase the recovery rate of resting patients.
With the power to return people from the very brink of death, these potions do not come cheaply.
These curative potions are too expensive for most civilians, and are used almost exclusively by soldiers and adventurers.
With the power to staunch the flow of blood or knit a broken bone, these potions are in common use among the dangerous professions.
This is a plate of cooked food, recently prepared. Enjoy!
This is a high quality smoking pipe.

Leather armor often used by followers of Shar or other dark deities
Leather armor often used by followers of Talos, Umberlee or other deities of sea or storms
